[1] WHO situation report 10 Dec 2014
Date: Wed 10 Dec 2014
Source: WHO [edited]
http://www.who.int/csr/disease/ebola/situation-reports/en


Ebola response roadmap - Situation report 10 Dec 2014
-----------------------------------------------------
Highlights
----------
- There have been 17 942 reported cases of Ebola virus disease (EVD), with 6388 reported deaths [as of 7 Dec 2014 (3 Dec in Liberia)].
[This is an increase of 797 cases and 318 deaths in a week (many unconfirmed). - Mod.JW]
- Case incidence is slightly increasing in Guinea, decreasing in Liberia, and may be increasing or stable in Sierra Leone.
- Sierra Leone now has the highest total number of reported cases of the 3 intense-transmission countries, with 7897 cases reported to date.
- At national level, Guinea, Liberia, and Sierra Leone have sufficient capacity to isolate and treat all reported EVD cases, and bury all EVD-related deaths safely and with dignity.
***However, local variations mean capacity is still insufficient in some areas. [emphasis added - ProMED]
... -- more

