[3] Sierra Leone: doctors strike settled
Date: Wed 10 Dec 2014
Source: Voice of America [edited]
http://www.voanews.com/content/junior-sierra-leone-doctors-on-a-partial-strike-over-ebola-protection/2552875.html


Junior Sierra Leone doctors on partial strike over Ebola protection
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Up to 8 Dec 2014, 106 medical personnel have died from Ebola in Sierra Leone, including 10 doctors, 3 of them as recently as last week. The doctors said they want a specialized Ebola unit equipped with a dialysis machine to treat them whenever they are infected by their patients and cannot be evacuated overseas. They also said they want an insurance policy. Sierra Leone's President Ernest Bai Koroma has assured junior doctors, who have been on a partial strike over the lack of proper care for local Ebola care givers, that their demands will be met.

Government spokesman Abdulai Bayraytay said President Koroma met [Tue 9 Dec 2014] with representatives of the Sierra Leone Doctors' Association and assured them their demands will be addressed immediately. Bayraytay said President Koroma told the doctors he appreciates their invaluable role in the fight against Ebola. "We, as a government, [have] already contacted the emergency hospitals. They have agreed that all that they (the doctors) have requested will be in the country around [17 Dec 2014]. The installation and everything will be up and running by [20 Dec 2014]," Bayraytay said.

[Byline: James Butty]

